      • getSupportedDeviceClasses

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Class<? extends ViewModel>> getSupportedDeviceClasses()
        Returns a list of Device class objects that are supported by this application. This list is used during device registration to provide a list of Device types that the user can choose from when registering a new device. The device classes returned from this method are instantiated using a dummy AylaDevice object and queried to provide the name of the device, the preferred registration type and an image representing the device. This information is gained from calling the following methods on each device returned from this method:
        • ViewModel.registrationType()
        • ViewModel.deviceTypeName()
        返回:
        A list of Class objects, one for each supported Device class
